  <name>FireDragon</name>
  <summary>Floorp fork build using custom branding &amp; settings</summary>
  <developer id="org.garudalinux.firedragon">
    <name>FireDragon Team</name>
  </developer>
  <description>
    <p>FireDragon is a browser based on the excellent Floorp browser. It was customized to have dr460nized-fitting aestetics as well as many opiniated settings by default. As this browser was originally a Librewolf fork, we are trying to integrate its best patches and tweaks in the new base. The most important features in addition of Floorps own ones can be found below.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Searx &amp; Whoogle search engines added, with the possibility to run locally</li>
      <li>The default search engine is Garuda's Searx instance</li>
      <li>Dark Reader</li>
      <li>Sweet theme added</li>
      <li>Custom, dr460nized branding üêâ</li>
      <li>Keeping settings in sync with Librewolfs changes</li>
      <li>Firefox accounts are enabled using a custom self-hosted sync server (ffsync.garudalinux.org)</li>
      <li>Faster webpages loading from: Custom Firedragon settings, Inclusion of FastFox tweaks</li>
      <li>Artwork by @SGS</li>
      <li>Hidden Navigation buttons instead of being greyed out when they are inactive</li>
      <li>Spoofing Chrome on Windows (through Floorp's User Agent switcher) when not using Fingerprinting</li>
      <li>PBMode Security</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
